Plan Your Database Model
Similarly to planning a front-end control flow, planning a database (or more specifically our
database models) is both crucial and challenging. Of course we can dive in and do everything on
the fly, but a couple of points to consider: A well planned database model can help us organize
data efficiently and effectively. If we define the structure of the database beforehand, we can
then ensure that we are storing our data efficiently and we have a blueprint for our code even
before we start writing code. With proper planning we can also work more efficiently rather than
making up data and relationships on the fly (and changing them on the fly as well!).
If we use our “Facebook for Dogs (and Their Owners)” as an example again. Let’s see how we
can start to model out our tables and relationships for the application.
Example on how to Model Data with MongoDB:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QAqK-R9HUhc
Example Data Model for the DogApp:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1w55hHFEfD5yhAQzR81eAMvXl0ufsfKeW/view?usp=sharing
Figma or StarUML are once again the right tools for the job here, but the data diagrams can be
made with something as simple as GoogleDocs.
Feel free to share your data model to your mentor. This can be either through github or google
docs discussing the structure of the data as well as possible challenges or shortcomings.
